Use the standard library
This is how to fruit_distribution of s and n:
   Remember that digits is "0123456789"
   Remember that numbers is []
   Remember that current is ""
   Remember that i is 0

   Do this s's length times:
      Remember that ch is item i in s
      When ch is in digits, then:
         Add current to ch
      But, if not:
         When current's length is more than 0, then:
            Add numbers to toint of current
            Remember that current is ""
         End when
      End when
      Increase i
   End do

   When current's length is more than 0, then:
      Add numbers to toint of current
   End when

   Remember that total_fruit is sum of numbers
   The answer is diff of n and total_fruit
Now you know

>>> fruit_distribution of "5 apples and 6 oranges" and 19
8
>>> fruit_distribution of "5 apples and 6 oranges" and 21
10